## Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)

1. **Use semantic HTML:**

```tsx
<button> not <div onClick>
<nav>, <main>, <footer>
<h1>, <h2>, <h3> in order
```

2. **Add ARIA labels:**

```tsx
<button aria-label="Close modal">
  <X />
</button>

// Live regions for dynamic content
<div aria-live="polite" role="status">
  {statusMessage}
</div>
```

3. **Keyboard navigation:**

```tsx
onKeyDown={(e) => {
  if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') {
    handleAction();
  }
}}
```

4. **Focus management:**

```tsx
// Trap focus in modals, return focus on close
// Use Radix UI Dialog/AlertDialog which handles this automatically
import { Dialog } from '@/components/ui/dialog';
```

5. **Color contrast:** Minimum 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text
6. **Motion:** Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` for animations
7. **Screen readers:** Test with VoiceOver (macOS) or NVDA (Windows)

